---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: "Visa Sponsorship Jobs FAQ — How It Works, Costs, and Timelines"
description: "Answers to the most common questions about visa sponsorship, relocation assistance, work permits, and how to find international tech jobs with visa support."
---

{% block structuredData %}
<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is visa sponsorship?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Visa sponsorship means an employer is willing to support your work visa application for their country. The company acts as your sponsor, often handling the paperwork and fees required for you to legally work in their country."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How do I apply for jobs on VisaJobs.xyz?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Browse the job listings, find a position that interests you, and click the Apply button. You'll be redirected to the employer's career page where you can submit your application directly."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is VisaJobs.xyz free to use?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes, VisaJobs.xyz is completely free for job seekers. You can browse all job listings, access resources, read blog articles, and subscribe to the newsletter without paying anything."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is relocation assistance?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Relocation assistance is support provided by employers to help new hires move to a different city or country. This can include financial support for moving expenses, temporary housing, flights, help finding permanent accommodation, language classes, and support for accompanying family members."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How long does visa processing take?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Visa processing times vary by country. EU Blue Card (Germany): 4-12 weeks. UK Skilled Worker Visa: 3-8 weeks. Canada Express Entry: 6-12 months. US H-1B Visa: 3-6 months if selected in lottery."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do I need to speak the local language?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "It depends on the country and role. Many tech companies in Northern and Western Europe operate in English. Countries like the Netherlands, Germany, and the Nordics have high English proficiency in the workplace. However, learning the local language is recommended for daily life and career advancement."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What countries are covered?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "VisaJobs.xyz lists jobs across 50+ countries, with a strong focus on popular tech destinations including Germany, the United Kingdom, the Netherlands, Canada, Ireland, Sweden, Switzerland, Australia, and many more."
      }
    }
  ]
}
</script>
{% endblock %}

<section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-brand-50 via-white to-indigo-50 dark:from-gray-950 dark:via-gray-900 dark:to-gray-950 py-16">
